{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_012hbvDuhXxiWSDeDaNSWNxF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete picture of the codebase. Here is the full implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Files to modify/create\n\n1. **New file:** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go`\n2. **Modify:** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go`\n3. **Modify:** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`\n4. **Modify:** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/install_istiocsr.go`\n5. **Modify:** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/utils.go`\n6. **New file:** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps_test.go`\n7. **Modify:** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments_test.go`\n\n---\n\n### 1. New file: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go`\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\n\n\tappsv1 \"k8s.io/api/apps/v1\"\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n)\n\n// readTrustedCABundle reads the CNO-injected CA bundle from the operator namespace.\n// Returns the PEM bundle and any error. Returns (\"\", nil) when the ConfigMap\n// does not exist (e.g. non-OpenShift clusters).\nfunc (r *Reconciler) readTrustedCABundle() (string, error) {\n\tcm := &corev1.ConfigMap{}\n\tkey := client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tNamespace: common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\tName:      common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName,\n\t}\n\tif err := r.Get(r.ctx, key, cm); err != nil {\n\t\tif errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", nil\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(\n\t\t\terr,\n\t\t\t\"failed to read CA bundle ConfigMap %q in namespace %q\",\n\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName, common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\t)\n\t}\n\n\tcaBundle := cm.Data[common.TrustedCABundleKey]\n\treturn caBundle, nil\n}\n\n// computeCABundleHash returns the SHA-256 hash of the CA bundle PEM content.\n// The hash is used as the pod template annotation to trigger rolling restarts\n// only when the actual certificate content changes.\nfunc computeCABundleHash(caBundle string) string {\n\thash := sha256.Sum256([]byte(caBundle))\n\treturn hex.EncodeToString(hash[:])\n}\n\n// updateCABundleHashAnnotation stamps the CA bundle content hash as a pod\n// template annotation to trigger a rolling restart when the bundle changes.\nfunc updateCABundleHashAnnotation(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, caBundleHash string) {\n\tif caBundleHash == \"\" {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif deployment.Spec.Template.Annotations == nil {\n\t\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Annotations = make(map[string]string)\n\t}\n\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Annotations[caBundleHashAnnotation] = caBundleHash\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Modify: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go`\n\nAdd the annotation constant inside the first `const` block (after `caVolumeMountPath` on line 27, or alongside the other annotation constants). Add this constant:\n\n```go\n// caBundleHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the\n// CNO-injected CA bundle hash for content-based rolling restarts.\ncaBundleHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-bundle-hash\"\n```\n\n**Exact diff** — insert after line 27 (`caVolumeMountPath = \"/var/run/configmaps/istio-csr\"`):\n\n```diff\n const (\n \tcaVolumeMountPath = \"/var/run/configmaps/istio-csr\"\n+\n+\t// caBundleHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the\n+\t// CNO-injected CA bundle hash for content-based rolling restarts.\n+\tcaBundleHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-bundle-hash\"\n )\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Modify: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`\n\n**Change 1** — `createOrApplyDeployments` signature (line 31): add `caBundleHash string` parameter.\n\n```diff\n-func (r *Reconciler) createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string, istioCSRCreateRecon bool) error {\n-\tdesired, err := r.getDep